        <!-- ===== PAGE 0: TEXT SUMMARIZATION ===== -->
        <div class="page active" id="page-0">
            <div class="page-header">
                <h2>üìù 1. Text Summarization</h2>
                <p>
                    The goal: take long content and compress it into something
                    short and clear. Two variations are shown ‚Äî one that
                    generates content, one that compresses existing content.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="prompt-wrap">
                <div class="lbl">
                    PROMPT ‚Äî VERSION 1 (Generate then summarize)
                </div>
                <pre><span class="hl-instruction">Explain antibiotics</span>

<span class="hl-output-ind">A:</span></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="output-wrap">
                <div class="lbl">OUTPUT</div>
                <pre>Antibiotics are a type of medication used to treat bacterial infections. They work by either killing the bacteria or preventing them from reproducing...</pre>
            </div>

            <div class="prompt-wrap">
                <div class="lbl">
                    PROMPT ‚Äî VERSION 2 (Summarize existing text)
                </div>
                <pre><span class="hl-input">Antibiotics are a type of medication used to treat bacterial infections. They work by either killing the bacteria or preventing them from reproducing, allowing the body's immune system to fight off the infection...</span>

<span class="hl-instruction">Explain the above in one sentence:</span></pre>
            </div>
            <div class="output-wrap">
                <div class="lbl">OUTPUT</div>
                <pre>Antibiotics are medications used to treat bacterial infections by either killing the bacteria or stopping them from reproducing, but they are not effective against viruses and overuse can lead to antibiotic resistance.</pre>
            </div>

            <div class="dissect">
                <div class="dissect-card used">
                    <h4>üîÆ What techniques were used?</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Output Indicator</strong> ("A:") ‚Äî signals to
                            the AI that an answer is expected, like a QA format
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Constraint instruction</strong> ("in one sentence")
                            ‚Äî limits the response length with a concrete rule
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Input-first pattern</strong> ‚Äî the text is given
                            first, then the instruction at the bottom tells the AI
                            what to do with it
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="dissect-card effect">
                    <h4>‚ö° How did it affect the output?</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            "A:" triggered a factual, informative response style
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            "in one sentence" forced the AI to compress and
                            prioritize ‚Äî it kept only the most essential facts
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Putting the text first then instruction after works
                            because AI reads everything before responding
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="dissect-card violate">
                    <h4>üí• What breaks if you remove it?</h4>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            Remove "in one sentence" ‚Üí AI gives a full paragraph
                            or even bullet points ‚Äî unpredictable length
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Remove "A:" ‚Üí AI might continue the sentence instead
                            of answering ("Antibiotics are‚Ä¶" just becomes a
                            completion)
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Put instruction before text ‚Üí AI might start
                            responding before "reading" the context
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="dissect-card bonus">
                    <h4>üéÅ Extra from me</h4>
